From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Disable testsuite timeout utility for Windows builds

The GHC source tarball doesn't include testsuite/timeout/, but Hadrian's
stage0Packages includes the timeout package on Windows. This causes builds
to fail when querying stagePackages because Hadrian tries to read the
non-existent testsuite/timeout/timeout.cabal file.

The timeout utility is only needed for running the testsuite, not for
building GHC itself. Since we don't run the testsuite during conda-forge
builds, we can safely exclude it from the package list.

This patch removes `timeout` from both stage0Packages and testsuitePackages.

--- a/hadrian/src/Settings/Default.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Settings/Default.hs
@@ -85,7 +85,8 @@
              , unlit
              ]
           ++ [ terminfo | not windowsHost, not cross ]
-          ++ [ timeout  | windowsHost                ]
+          -- Disabled: timeout is in testsuite/ which is not in source tarball
+          -- ++ [ timeout  | windowsHost                ]
           ++ [ touchy   | windowsHost                ]
           ++ [ hp2ps    | cross                      ]

@@ -137,7 +138,8 @@

 -- | Packages that are built only for the testsuite.
 testsuitePackages :: Action [Package]
-testsuitePackages = return ([ timeout | windowsHost ] ++ [ checkPpr, checkExact ])
+-- Disabled: timeout is in testsuite/ which is not in source tarball
+testsuitePackages = return [ checkPpr, checkExact ]

 -- | Default build ways for library packages:
 -- * We always build 'vanilla' way.
